As the Charleston area population grows, so do the needs for an experienced, real estate professional for guidance through this highly competitive sales market. Contact Pam Harrington Exclusives for your next sale or purchase and truly experience the difference.

Today, Gama Aviation employs over 1400 people worldwide at over 45 locations in 17 countries across five continents, making it one of the world’s leading aviation services companies. In January 2017, Gama Aviation Plc and BBA Aviation Plc announced the merger their US charter and aircraft management business interests resulting in Gama Aviation LLC taking over all operations of the Landmark Aviation Aircraft management and charter business.
